question:
District category contains Historic Downtown, Legal District, Shopping District, and Tech Park.
Supermarkets category contains Trader Joe's, and Giant Eagle.
Product category contains Smoothies, Yogurt, and Pudding.
The number of each Tech Park 's Trader Joe's equals 1.
The number of each Trader Joe's 's Yogurt equals 9.
The number of each Historic Downtown 's Giant Eagle equals 19.
The number of each Shopping District 's Trader Joe's equals each Historic Downtown 's Trader Joe's.
The number of each Legal District 's Trader Joe's equals 1.
The number of each Shopping District 's Giant Eagle equals the difference of each Historic Downtown 's Giant Eagle and each Historic Downtown 's Trader Joe's.
The number of each Giant Eagle 's Smoothies equals 0.
The number of each Giant Eagle 's Yogurt equals 9 more than the difference of each Trader Joe's 's Pudding and each Historic Downtown 's Giant Eagle.
The number of each Trader Joe's 's Pudding equals 19 times each Shopping District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Legal District 's Giant Eagle equals 8.
The number of each Tech Park 's Giant Eagle equals 5 times the difference of each Legal District 's Trader Joe's and each Legal District 's Giant Eagle.
The number of each Historic Downtown 's Trader Joe's equals 11.
How many Yogurt does Giant Eagle have?
solution:
Define each Historic Downtown 's Trader Joe's as t; So t = 11.
Define each Shopping District 's Trader Joe's as I; So I = t = 11.
Define each Historic Downtown 's Giant Eagle as h; So h = 19.
Define each Shopping District 's Giant Eagle as V; So V = h - t = 19 - 11 = 8.
Define each Shopping District 's Supermarkets as j; So j = V + I = 8 + 11 = 19.
Define each Trader Joe's 's Pudding as T; So T = 19 * j = 19 * 19 = 16.
Define each Giant Eagle 's Yogurt as Z; D = T - h = 16 - 19 = 20; So Z = 9 + D = 9 + 20 = 6.
